 one of Canada's most popular products. It offers original insights on consumer culture, mass consumption, and the dynamics of Canadian history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aConsumption (Economics)zCanadaxHistory. 0aDoughnutsxSocial aspectszCanada. 0aFast food restaurantsxEconomic aspectszCanada. 0aFast food restaurantsxSocial aspectszCanada. 0aFranchises (Retail trade)zCanadaxHistory. 4aCoursebook. 7aHISTORY / Canada / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311049095440uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144268792940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442687929423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781442687929/original  a978-3-11-049095-4  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK